Welcome to October's Turing-Roche newsletter! Here you can find what's new in the Turing-Roche strategic partnership and opportunities, events and news from both The Alan Turing Institute and Roche.

Our [five year partnership](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FpZtEXUtPPy7zoQQw3kgPMA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280068973163%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=u0z5BP%2FebI2d5Fwhjh67qTpyvAwUnxZ1xxB8Pyvy%2FNs%3D&reserved=0) was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FtwKFKRCjk8Koqj_vb-rn9g&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280068973163%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=YXqN75ouzCsyFC9RPL8LuPT1B%2FVk0iduZTl1ameQDIc%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment. Our 'North Star' is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care. **

We will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

If you have anything you'd like featured in a future newsletter then please get in touch with Vicky Hellon, Community Manager for the partnership at <vhellon@turing.ac.uk>

If you would like to share this newsletter with relevant colleagues please direct them to sign-up [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FumVURmo5qRTDnu_99NIPIQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280068973163%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=qTDn9J9YduTKThrNbxr51JOqR2gifXW7zgW8IwRGHo8%3D&reserved=0).

### Knowledge Share Series Event: AI in Precision Medicine

**10 October 2022**

Join us for our [partnership knowledge share series](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FMX9XAw6Qxmz6SKm7SEDB4Q&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280068973163%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=dbTLkDT3uQ1iCGm4QZAU4BbMQz1SwordCDZjyP6NvXs%3D&reserved=0). Our aim is to bring together members of the Turing and Roche networks and the wider scientific community to share different academic and industry perspectives on areas related to patient/treatment heterogeneity and data science more generally.

October's event is on the 10th on theme of AI in Precision Medicine. We'll be hearing from Dr Samaneh Abbasi, Senior Data Scientist and Data Science Network Co-Lead on the PHC Data analytics and Imaging (DAI) team at Roche and Professor Zoe Kourtzi, Professor of Cognitive Computational Neuroscience at the University of Cambridge and Turing University Lead. You can register for the event [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2Fl70pufDkupyQpZJWpPYF-w&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280068973163%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=rixutVs%2BDJB%2FjwsYJQRkMuV2NKZGJuMUoFZeSvVChO0%3D&reserved=0).

You can also catch-up on previous recordings of our events at our [YouTube channel](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FvvK0Uy44NSAXodrGUOC75Q&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280068973163%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=bUPSs64lMctJU2YTR6uZ52MdkpBbDCpjneZiNbxNU%2BQ%3D&reserved=0).

### Partnership funding call on Predictive Modelling

The partnership has launched a funding call in the topic of predictive modelling in the context of uncertainty and heterogeneity in biomedical data and we are inviting proposals from researchers. Projects can either be main projects- running for 12-18 months and aimed at senior researchers, or pilot projects- running for approx 6 months for early career researchers looking to pursue proof-of-concept research.

You can find out more about the funding call and how to apply [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPVl4amh0dEFfc1llWFVYc1RGYzFENVNaWXhPWEFsQkdIWjluZ1BsRzhGVFZwTkIyS1dHdXVVNVJuNUt2WXJzWmImcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi04ZWUwZDM0NDIzZWU0YzliYjkyMzU0ZDUzNTNiNjZmNCZlc2lkPWUzZjE3MmU0LTc1NDUtZWQxMS1iYmEzLTAwMjI0ODNmNzIzMSJ9%2FQIKYzuXSVPIW0d5IICBUBA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280068973163%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=2i4LyJ6%2Fo0u%2FBtRXohzbMlSdDbkKfp3Ze%2FrSWXoEcdQ%3D&reserved=0). You can also catchup on our information and Q&A session that we ran about the call [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FE7LNnItNVKPw4fI4Wjt1yQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280069137657%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=Sj8%2BS4HVVobRroffsW2XOpsetNMSmFOVD0xgadvPGac%3D&reserved=0).

### Turing Institute AI Standards Hub Launch

**12 October 2022**

The Turing Institute is launching the AI Standards Hub- the UK's new initiative dedicated to knowledge sharing, community building, strategic research, and international engagement around standardisation for AI technologies. The initiative is led by the Alan Turing Institute in partnership with the British Standards Institution (BSI), the National Physical Laboratory (NPL) and supported by the Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport (DCMS) and the Office for AI. You can register for the launch event [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FjxQ6nIo6pwLlLM829CJP7w&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280069444568%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=byDEBMmqxqB1j0W1BnWKYbGr1YIWiu09COFcJ7TAjMI%3D&reserved=0), which will showcase the interactive online platform and will have presentations and interactive discussions with senior government representatives, the Hub's partner organizations, and key stakeholders.

### Fairness in Healthcare Modelling Course by Health Data Research UK (HDR UK)

**Registration Deadline 15 October 2022**

**Course 9-11 November 2022**

Led by Professor Ionna Manolopoulou from UCL, this free, in-person course aims to cover the basic principles of fairness in healthcare modelling and highlight aspects of fairness that Health Data Scientists need to be aware of in their own research. Participants should be current PhD students at a UK university, experienced in graduate-level studies in mathematics, statistics and computational science and proficient in a modern programming language (particularly Python and/or R). Find out more about this course and others run by the HDR UK PhD Programme [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPVl4amh0dEFfc1llWFVYc1RGYzFENVNaWXhPWEFsQkdIWjluZ1BsRzhGVFZwTkIyS1dHdXVVNVJuNUt2WXJzWmImcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi04ZWUwZDM0NDIzZWU0YzliYjkyMzU0ZDUzNTNiNjZmNCZlc2lkPWUzZjE3MmU0LTc1NDUtZWQxMS1iYmEzLTAwMjI0ODNmNzIzMSJ9%2FYE9ZgjwzMTlvUvx66QVh8g&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280069444568%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=pQ88IzQvvig7n8dcwaauqUBZu2fByZboB0HgOdGzImg%3D&reserved=0).

## Publication of the Month
![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/patrick-tomasso-oaqk7qqnh_c-unsplash2.jpg)

**Integrated multimodal artificial intelligence framework for healthcare applications**

October's publication of the month from MIT Researcher Dimitris Bertsimas and colleagues describes a Holistic AI in Medicine (HAIM) framework that facilitates the generation and testing of AI systems that leverage multimodal inputs. Their approach uses generalizable data pre-processing and machine learning modeling stages that can be readily adapted for research and deployment in healthcare environments. The paper is published in npj digital medicine and you can read it [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPVl4amh0dEFfc1llWFVYc1RGYzFENVNaWXhPWEFsQkdIWjluZ1BsRzhGVFZwTkIyS1dHdXVVNVJuNUt2WXJzWmImcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi04ZWUwZDM0NDIzZWU0YzliYjkyMzU0ZDUzNTNiNjZmNCZlc2lkPWUzZjE3MmU0LTc1NDUtZWQxMS1iYmEzLTAwMjI0ODNmNzIzMSJ9%2FvYa_f-TZQlBXa697XiQjsw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C1e700abb662b4df5718308daa83daad6%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638007280069600834%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=%2BKwo358XilRGxPPuKeR1uEZSk3Y%2BOZOCn8r2TLRnLh4%3D&reserved=0).
